                            <comment id="424097" author="adilger" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2024 21:37:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would still be useful to implement this, because the current code risks request corruption if the __u32 field overlapping rr_mirror_id is ever used, and at some point we will want to use another __u32 field in mdt_rec_reint and we will wish that this had been implemented sooner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="423728" author="flei" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 02:12:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is not urgent today because nanosecond timestamp code replaces &lt;tt&gt;rr_a/m/ctime&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;rr_a/m/ctime_ns&lt;/tt&gt; and no additional space is needed in &lt;tt&gt;mdt_rec_reint&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
